## What's in the box

```
.
├── app.py                          FastAPI entrypoint + audit middleware
├── app.yaml                        runtime config (host, port, env, resource bindings)
├── databricks.yml                  bundle: dev + prod targets, Lakebase binding
├── permissions.yaml                declarative grants — applied automatically on deploy
├── alembic.ini                     migration tooling
├── migrations/                     versioned schema changes (downgrade() is mandatory)
├── server/
│   ├── auth/                       OBO + SP helpers
│   ├── db/                         Lakebase pool with OAuth refresh
│   ├── middleware/                 audit logger (auto JSON per request)
│   └── routes/                     health/env routes; add yours here
├── scripts/
│   ├── apply_grants.py             post-deploy SP grant runner
│   ├── lakebase_branch.py          PR branch lifecycle
│   └── rollback_migration.py       alembic + branch-swap rollback
├── logs-sink/                      workspace-wide audit pipeline (deploy once)
├── docs/
│   ├── ARCHITECTURE.md             read this first
│   ├── RUNBOOK.md                  common ops
│   └── DATA_CLASSIFICATION.md      what goes in UC vs Lakebase
├── .github/workflows/
│   ├── validate.yml                PR: blocks hardcoded values, validates bundle
│   ├── deploy.yml                  main: migrate -> deploy -> grant -> restart -> smoke
│   └── branch-per-pr.yml           per-PR Lakebase branch + migration test
└── .claude/CLAUDE.md               binding rules for AI-assisted edits
```

## Quick start

1. Set up GitHub Environments and the variables/secrets listed in
   [`docs/RUNBOOK.md`](docs/RUNBOOK.md#first-time-setup-per-repo-once).
2. Deploy once locally for the initial app provisioning:
   ```bash
   databricks bundle validate -t dev
   databricks bundle deploy -t dev
   python scripts/apply_grants.py --app-name {{.app_name}}
   databricks apps restart {{.app_name}}
   ```
3. From there on, **all deploys go through GitHub Actions.** No exceptions.

## Deploy the workspace-wide log sink (once per workspace, not per app)

```bash
cd logs-sink
databricks bundle deploy -t prod
```

All apps from this template will start showing up in
`{{.audit_catalog}}.audit.app_events`.

